Summary[dnd-info]=The Gharoni Highlands, situated to the northwest of the Elda Reem Passlands, unveils a majestic expanse of sweeping plains and rolling hills. This province boasts an untamed wilderness that teems with diverse wildlife, creating a haven for magnificent creatures such as zebras, horses, rhinoceroses, and other unique fauna. The vast grasslands stretch as far as the eye can see, painting the landscape in vibrant hues of green, gold, and amber. Among the prominent features of the Gharoni Highlands are the enigmatic standing stones scattered across the plains, believed to hold ancient significance and mysterious powers. These monolithic structures, weathered by time, evoke a sense of reverence and awe, drawing occasional pilgrims and curious explorers who seek to uncover their secrets. The air in the Gharoni Highlands carries the sweet scent of wildflowers that blanket the meadows, providing a vibrant tapestry of colors and attracting butterflies and hummingbirds in abundance. The few small towns and villages that dot the region are humble and close-knit, deeply connected to the land and its natural rhythms. The people of the Gharoni Highlands live in harmony with nature, relying on its resources for sustenance and crafting, displaying remarkable skills in horsemanship and animal husbandry. The province offers an immersive experience of untouched beauty and a serene respite from the bustling cities and grand civilizations found elsewhere, making it a haven for adventurers, nature enthusiasts, and those seeking solace in the embrace of the untamed wilderness.

